Since February 14, 2019, when he made a re-entry into the Nigerian and the global music scene with ‘Odo,’ singer Ubin T. Mackson, now known as Binny Boy, has not slowed down his trajectory. Riding on the public appeal his music has garnered so far, the Taraba State-born artist has hinted that he is set to release a new project, details of which he said he is keeping close to his chest. With two tentative titles, ‘Ma Laide’ or ‘Pop to your Speaker’, the singer stated that the new project draws from his emotions.   Wife to donate kidney to Eedris Abdulkareem     ‘Peter Obi can only win on Twitter’     Mixed reactions over PSquare’s comeback songs   “I see my music as a tool to send a message to people. A message of peace, hope, and inspiration. All of these elements have weighed in strongly in the new project. It is my own contribution to building a better society. As humans, we can never stop trying,” Binny Boy said. His song, ‘Odo’ received massive airplay and recognition in the UK, pushing him to a person of interest in the music industry. Binny Boy quickly followed this up with ‘Saturday’ which cemented his place as someone to watch out for, gaining buzz throughout the summer of 2019 in the UK and Nigeria. Binny Boy is currently signed to and co-owns Luminary Vision Records. Binny Boy’s dream has always been to be a musician. A singer, songwriter, audio engineer & business mogul, Binny Boy started his musical journey at the age of 15 along with his friends.